
  <sn><md>#### Hebrew Civilization

:::.row
:::.col-12 .col-md-6
The Hebrew civilization developed around the `city of Jerusalem in Palestine`. **Hebrew** is `not` the name of a `race`,it is a Semitic `language`. People `who spoke this language` were known as ++Hebrews++.<br> 
The *original homeland* of the Hebrews was the `Arabian desert`.<br> The *present inhabitants* of Israel are `descendants of the Hebrews`.<br> The Hebrews *contributed* mainly in the field of `religion`.<br> They were the first to widely `promote monotheism` (belief in one God). However, long before this, `Pharaoh Akhenaten` of Egypt had also called for the *worship of a single god*, but it did not become popular. The prophets of the Hebrews—Hazrat Musa (A.), Hazrat Dawud (A.), and Hazrat Sulaiman (A.)—brought a major transformation in religious consciousness.
